title: Bachelorette Sam Frost denies rumours of heartache
text:
Bachelorette Sam Frost denies rumours of heartache Seanna Cronin | 20th Oct 2015 4:30 PM Seanna Cronin APN Entertainment Editor A US ex-pat, Seanna has been writing about the Australian entertainment industries for the past six years and is also a documentary producer, photographer and scuba diver. Sam Frost stars in the TV series The Bachelorette. Channel 10 Local Real Estate 
SAM Frost has taken to her Instagram account to deny rumours of post-Bachelorette heartache. 
Interest is ramping up as fans prepare for the final two episodes of the show to air tomorrow and Thursday nights on Channel 10. 
Frost's post was in response to a story published by New Idea magazine yesterday claiming she had picked the wrong guy in the show's finale, which has already been filmed in New Zealand. 
"I can confirm, I'm not pregnant, confused or had a change of heart," Frost wrote. 
"It's been four months, my man and I are still going strong and very happy together." 
She also tweeted about her excitement about finally being able to go public with her "gorgeous boyfriend". 
Frost warned fans tomorrow's rose ceremony, where she will farewell one of her final three suitors, will be her most emotional yet. The Bachelorette Sam Frost with the show's finalists, from left, Richie, Sasha and Michael. Channel 10 
There doesn't seem to be a clear favourite according to the fan-voted love leader board on the show's official website. 
"Wednesday night is absolutely heart-breaking," she wrote. 
"(A) very sad moment saying goodbye to a truly incredible man." channel 10
